
meta-rno-g
============

AKA EeVanescent Linux. 

This layer contains customizations on top of meta-ampliphy/meta-phytec for the RNO-G experiment when using the AM62X SOM

The top-level image is called rno-g-station-sd

To use, you probably want to set up the environment as specified on the on the phytec website, set machine to rno-g-revn, distro to eevanescent, then add this layer.

Then bitbake rno-g-station-sd for an SD card image or rno-g-station-emmc for an EMMC image. Note that the SD card is set up as a one-shot flasher.

More documentation forthcoming, someday.



